      "hash":"conditions",
      "title": "Range of Services",
      "body": "Our service includes the diagnosis and treatment of problems arising from hip disorders that started in childhood and the full range of surgery for arthritis.",
      "content": [
        {
          "id":"1",
          "icon": "",
          "class": "icon-button",
          "title": "Primary Replacement",
          "body": "A hip replacement is a surgical procedure in which the hip joint is replaced by a prothetic implant. It is generally conducted to relieve arthritis pain or hip fractures."
        },
        {
          "id":"2",
          "icon": "",
          "title": "Revision Surgery",
          "class": "icon-button",
          "body": "Hip revision surgery involves replacing the artificial hip joint if it has become loose, infected or worn out."
        },
        {
          "id":"3",
          "icon": "",
          "title": "Hip Reconstruction",
          "class": "icon-button",
          "body": "Hip reconstructive surgery is a surgical procedure done to restore your mobility and alleviate hip pain."
        },
        {
          "id":"4",
          "icon": "",
          "title": "Joint Revision",
          "class": "icon-button",
          "body": "A revision joint replacement is a surgical procedure to replace a worn out joint replacement."
        },
        {
          "id":"5",
          "icon": "",
          "title": "Osteotomy",
          "class": "icon-button",
          "body": "An osteotomy is a surgical operation whereby a bone is cut to shorten or lengthen it or to change its alignment."
        }
      ]
    },
