    {
      "id"  : "3",
      "hash" : "pathway",
      "title" : "Your Journey",
      "body"  : "Your patient pathway starts with a referral by your local GP or District General Hospital and  continues until your treatment is completed.",
      "image" : "service_journey",
      "video" : "service_hip_journey",
      "pathway" : [
        {
          "hash" : "admission",
          "title": "Admission",
          "content": [
            {
              "id": "1",
              "icon": "bf-journey-nilbymouth",
              "header": "Nil by Mouth",
              "body": "Prior to surgery please do not have any liquids or foods. This may even be 24 hours beforehand."
            },
            {
              "id": "2",
              "icon": "bf-journey-whattobring",
              "header": "What to bring",
              "body": "Please bring the following items with you: Medication & tablets, toiletries & towels, dressing gown, change of clothes, pyjamas, slippers"
            },
            {
              "id": "3",
              "icon": "bf-journey-appointment",
              "header": "Date of Admission",
              "body": "Upon arrival at the admissions lounge we will tell you about the ward and its location. You will be seen by your consultant or a member of his team and have the opportunity to ask any final questions about your surgery."
            },
            {
              "id": "4",
              "icon": "bf-journey-injection",
              "header": "Anaesthetics",
              "body": "We will also explain and talk to you about the anaesthetics you will have administered."
            },
            {
              "id": "5",
              "icon": "bf-journey-consent",
              "header": "Consent",
              "body": "Once you are happy you will be ask to sign a consent form. A mark will be drawn on the hip to indicate which side and area is being operated on."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "hash" : "stay",
          "title": "During your stay",
          "content": [
            {
              "id": "1",
              "icon": "bf-journey-checkin",
              "header": "Check in Ward",
              "body": "Please hand in your medication to the nurse and change into a hospital gown, stockings & pants. The nurse will also check your general well being (blood pressure, heart rate, etc)."
            },
            {
              "id": "2",
              "icon": "bf-journey-theatre",
              "header": "Theatre",
              "body": "The nurse and porter will take you to the theatre where you will meet the anaesthetist who will guide you off to sleep. "
            },
            {
              "id": "3",
              "icon": "bf-journey-surgery",
              "header": "Surgery",
              "body": "You then have your surgery."
            },
            {
              "id": "4",
              "icon": "bf-journey-recovery",
              "header": "Recovery",
              "body": "When you wake up the first person you see is the recovery nurse who is there to make sure you are okay and in no pain. You may go to the high dependency unit overnight for monitoring."
            },
            {
              "id": "5",
              "icon": "bf-journey-ward",
              "header": "Ward",
              "body": "A member of the team will come and see you after surgery to explain what took place."
            },
            {
              "id": "6",
              "icon": "bf-journey-medication",
              "header": "Medication",
              "body": "You will be given suitable pain relief to help with early mobilisation. Please take your laxatives to assist your bowel movement and prevent constipation."
            },
            {
              "id": "7",
              "icon": "bf-journey-physiotherapy",
              "header": "Physiotherapist",
              "body": "A physiotherapist will come and see you to get you up and out of bed and advise how much weight you are allowed to put through your new hip. This is important to minimise post operative complications and speed up your recovery."
            },
            {
              "id": "8",
              "icon": "bf-journey-support",
              "header": "Occupational Therapist",
              "body": "You will also be visited by the occupational therapist to advise you about how to manage daily activities such as washing and getting dressed."
            },
            {
              "id": "9",
              "icon": "bf-journey-paindiary",
              "header": "Precaution",
              "body": "We will also remind you of the hip precautions for you to follow for the first 12 weeks after your operation. You are provided with your medication before being discharged home."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "hash" : "discharge",
          "title": "Discharge",
          "content": [
            {
              "id": "1",
              "icon": "bf-journey-checkup",
              "header": "Check up",
              "body": "Two weeks after surgery please ensure you have arranged an appointment with your GP practice or district nurse to have your wound checked and your clips or sutures removed."
            },
            {
              "id": "2",
              "icon": "bf-journey-appointment",
              "header": "Appointment",
              "body": "After your wound has healed at about 2-3 weeks you will be seen by an outpatients physiotherapist to progress your excise if required."
            },
            {
              "id": "3",
              "icon": "bf-journey-advice",
              "header": "Advice",
              "body": "You will be required to wear your anti-embolism stockings for 6 weeks after your operation to reduce the threat of blood clots forming in your legs whilst less active than normal."
            },
            {
              "id": "4",
              "icon": "bf-journey-injection",
              "header": "Pain Relief",
              "body": "We will advise you to gradually reduce your levels of pain relief with guidance from your GP."
            },
            {
              "id": "5",
              "icon": "bf-journey-assessment",
              "header": "Assessment",
              "body": "Your first appointment after surgery will be in 6-8 weeks time when you will see the consultant or a member of their team to assess your progress."
            },
            {
              "id": "6",
              "icon": "bf-journey-xray",
              "header": "X Ray",
              "body": "If you require an X Ray please make ensure to arrive 30 minutes before your appointment.  Certain restrictions may be lifted at this point in time."
            },
            {
              "id": "7",
              "icon": "bf-journey-conclusion",
              "header": "Conclusion",
              "body": "Once your treatment has been deemed successful you will be discharged back to your GP."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },

